                {"src": "clarke", "attr": "Clarke's Commentary", "html": "<p>Blessed are they whose iniquities are forgiven — that is, the man is truly happy whose iniquities, <em>hai anomiai</em>, whose transgressions of the law are forgiven; for by these he was exposed to the most grievous punishment. Whose sins, <em>hai hamartiai</em>, his innumerable deviations from the strict rule of truth and righteousness, are covered — entirely removed out of sight, and thrown into oblivion.</p>"},
