                {"src": "clarke", "attr": "Clarke's Commentary", "html": "<p>Now it was not written for his sake alone — the fact of Abraham's believing and receiving salvation through that faith is not recorded as a mere circumstance in the patriarch's life intended to do him honor: see Romans 4:24. The mention of this circumstance has a much more extensive design than merely to honor Abraham. It is recorded as the model according to which God will save both Jews and Gentiles.</p>"},
